  "sn2.7:1.1": "Linked Discourses 2",
  "sn2.7:2.1": "1 The Sun",
  "sn2.7:3.1": "7 With Pañcālacaṇḍa",
  "sn2.7:4.1": "At Sāvatthī.",
  "sn2.7:4.2": "Standing to one side, the god Pañcālacaṇḍa recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:",
  "sn2.7:5.1": "“The opening amid confinement",
  "sn2.7:5.2": "was discovered by the Buddha of vast intelligence,",
  "sn2.7:5.3": "who woke up to absorption,",
  "sn2.7:5.4": "the sage, the solitary bull.”",
  "sn2.7:6.1": "“Even amid confinement they discover,” said the Buddha to Pañcālacaṇḍa,",
  "sn2.7:6.2": "“the principle for attaining extinguishment.",
  "sn2.7:6.3": "Those who have acquired mindfulness",
  "sn2.7:6.4": "are perfectly converged in samādhi.”"
}